# .docs-lint — denylist of tokens that must never reappear in the docs once
# they're cut from the code. Copy to your repo root as `.docs-lint` and seed
# it as you remove things. One POSIX extended-regex per line; '#' comments and
# blank lines ignored. Changelog/history files are exempt. Checked by
# scripts/check-docs.sh.
#
# The point: when you delete an env var, rename a crate, or kill a feature,
# add its name here. A stale doc that names it again then fails CI instead of
# rotting silently. Examples (delete these, add your own):

# old env var the code no longer reads
# MYAPP_LEGACY_TIMEOUT

# deleted service/crate
# myapp-http-bridge

# renamed binary (regex-escape the dot)
# myapp-old-cli\b

# dead doc path you repointed
# docs/OLD_GUIDE\.md
